    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PDCCH channel estimation array parameter ordering\n\n### Summary\nIn the NR PDCCH processing chain, the `nr_pdcch_channel_compensation` function call had its second and third parameters swapped. Both parameters are similarly-typed `int32_t` arrays (`rxdataF_ext` and `dl_ch_estimates_ext`) which led to channel estimates being passed where received data was expected, and vice versa.\n\nThis caused incorrect PDCCH decoding and potential false DCI detection during sustained operation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_TRANSPORT/dci_nr.c`: Corrected parameter order in `nr_pdcch_channel_compensation` call within `nr_rx_pdcch` function.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Run NR PDCCH decoding with active DL traffic\n2. Monitor DCI false detection rate over time\n3. Observe increased false positives due to incorrect channel compensation\n4. Memory inspection would show channel estimate data being used in rxdata processing paths\n\n"
}